ith API 6 for this.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test scanning issues**\\n\\nI’m considering how TestAotProcessor.scanClasspathRoots scans everything without a package filter. It seems like it will also scan tests, including class templates. If there’s a nested static class with @ClassTemplate and @ContextConfiguration that has @Test, it could be treated as a JUnit test. I wonder if a static nested class inside a top-level package-private static class could be discovered as a test and executed by JUnit?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_oxGxqMD9Q9R3yxoePZRYWeSL|fc_0a9e76e99fd0de06016a28c02e4df481908283fa3655c93bac", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "JAR=$(find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.junit.jupiter/junit-jupiter-params/6.0.0 -type f -name '*.jar' | head -1); jar tf \"$JAR\" | grep 'org/junit/jupiter/params' | grep 'Class\\|Parameter' | sed -n '1,120p' && javap -classpath \"$JAR\" org.junit.jupiter.params.Parameter org.junit.jupiter.params.ParameterizedClass org.junit.jupiter.params.provider.ValueSource", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 636, "output": 1528, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34932, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781055500610, "responseId": "resp_0a9e76e99fd0de06016a28c00d5b6c81909173737dae966199"}}
