*Evaluating inner classes**\\n\\nI’m noticing that `@Nested` classes cannot be static, which is good since they are package-private inner classes. However, there's a potential issue with `ClassUtils.isInnerClass` returning true for both static and non-static classes. I wonder if Spring considers this to be true only for non-static cases. To clarify, I'll check how collection checks work with `getDeclaredClasses` and `@Nested`, especially since JUnit’s `@Nested` does require non-static classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating native image testing**\\n\\nI'm contemplating how JUnit tests execute within a native image. It seems there's no classpath root, and the previous tests don't invoke the scanner. This might lead to failures because of that classpath root condition. I wonder if the tests in TCK run as executable with a classpath while the test classes are embedded in the image, not on the filesystem. It raises questions about dynamic-access coverage from Java run and whether we can catch unsupported features related to class loading. The lack of classpath scanning could be a concern.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering build-time behavior**\\n\\nI'm wondering if requiring file system roots is actually a build-time behavior rather than something that runs at native runtime. It seems like classpath scanning of classes isn't supported under native conditions, which complicates things. I could catch an UnsupportedFeatureError, but maybe failures would be assertions due to the absence of roots instead of errors. The existing dynamic access framework certainly wants the tests to run in a native context. This presents a bit of a challenge!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_SBxG9DZH9aeJxfzC1mjz95ci|fc_0a9e76e99fd0de06016a28c05001348190aa93fb3ef01a178c", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "grep -R \"NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError\" -n tests/src | head -30 && grep -R \"getCodeSource\\|getResource(\\\".*class\" -n tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/src/test/java | head -50", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2614, "output": 1333, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37227, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781055535943, "responseId": "resp_0a9e76e99fd0de06016a28c030866c8190a70d9297d596f103"}}
